7) Use example for time documentations
<?php
//begin config area
date_default_timezone_set('America/Los_Angeles');

//create variables
$time = date('H');  //H is	24-hour format of an hour with leading zeros 00 through 23

8)Use an if/else statement

$color = "green";
$comment = "Youre Lebowski, Im The Dude!";
if($time==18)
{
    $color="Pink";
    $comment="Walter":
}



$color = "green";
$comment = "Youre Lebowski, Im The Dude!";

9) Here we used an if/else statement to accomodate a 24 hour period
$time = date('H');  //H is	24-hour format of an hour with leading zeros 00 through 23
if($time==22)
{
    $color="Pink";
    $comment="Walter";
}else{
    $color="Yellow";
    $comment="Donny";
}

9)Here we used a switch condition to allow more flexability

switch()
{
    case 18:
    $color="Pink";
    $comment="Walter";   
    break;
        
    case 19:
    $color="Purple";
    $comment="Jeffery";   
    break;   
        
    default: 
    $color="Black";
    $comment="The Big Lebowski"; 
?>



<html>

    <body>

        <h1>The Time is: <?=$time?> <!--this is a "short tag" WITHOUT ;--> </h1>    
        <p>This hour's color is: <?=$color?></p> 
        <p>Interesting comment goes here: <?=$comment?></p>

    </body>

    

</html>